Package api

Class DWGraph_Algo

java.lang.Object
api.DWGraph_Algo
All Implemented Interfaces:
dw_graph_algorithms
public class DWGraph_Algo
extends java.lang.Object
implements dw_graph_algorithms
This class was created in order to implement several algorithms of a weighted directed graph. For some of these functions I created using several well known algorithms, more information about it can be found in the Wiki area of the repository.

    • getTransposedGraph

      public directed_weighted_graph getTransposedGraph()
      This function was built in order to create a transposed graph and use it in the isConnected function. In summary, this function switches the direction of each edge in the graph and returns the transposed graph.
      Returns:
      - The transposed graph.

    • isConnected

      public boolean isConnected()
      This function checks the connectivity of a graph and whether its strongly connected (given that its a directed graph). Using help from the DFS algorithms and the getTransposedGraph function, this function checks the traversal of the graph and if every node was visited, and after transposing the graph, if again every node is visited in the traversal.
      Specified by:
      isConnected in interface dw_graph_algorithms
      Returns:
      - If the graph is strongly connected or not.

    • shortestPathDist

      public double shortestPathDist​(int src, int dest)
      Using Dijkstra's algorithm this function returns the total sum of the traversal of the edges of the shortest path between two nodes in the graph. If no such path exists, the function returns -1.
      Specified by:
      shortestPathDist in interface dw_graph_algorithms
      Parameters:
      src - - start node of the path
      dest - - end (target) node of the path
      Returns:
      - The total sum weight of all the edges in the path.

    • shortestPath

      public java.util.List<node_data> shortestPath​(int src, int dest)
      Using Dijkstra's algorithm this function returns a list of the path that occurred during the traversal of the nodes of the shortest path between two nodes in the graph. If no such path exists, the function returns null.
      Specified by:
      shortestPath in interface dw_graph_algorithms
      Parameters:

      dest - - end (target) node of the path
      Returns:

    • dijkstra_algo

      public void dijkstra_algo​(int src, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer> ParentsList, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Double> DistanceList)
      This is an implementation of Dijkstra's algorithm in order to traverse through the graph and find the shortest path from the source node given in the input, to the rest of the nodes in the graph.
      Parameters:
      src - - The source node of the traversal of the graph.
      ParentsList - - A HashMap that contains each node and its direct parent in the graph.
      DistanceList - - A HashMap that contains each node and its distance from the source node.
